      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "**<strong>**\n\n**Disclaimer:** Since I am an AI, this is a fictional, in-character piece of dialogue and does not constitute medical advice.\n\n**[SCENE START]**\n\n**INT. DOCTOR'S WAITING ROOM/EXAM ROOM - DAY**\n\nThe room is overly bright, perhaps a little too cheerful. DR. RICKY FLUSTER (40s), impossibly tanned, wearing athleisure wear that looks suspiciously expensive and a smirk permanently affixed to his face, leans against a counter. He exudes effortless, overconfident energy—a veritable peacock of medical swagger.\n\nFLUSTER\n(Waving a dismissive hand, like swatting a gnat)\nNah, nah, nah. Hold up there, pal. Insulin dosage? Please. What are we talking about?\n\nThe \"Patient,\" MARK (30s), sits gingerly on the examination table. He is visibly uncomfortable: his hands are trembling slightly, a sheen of sweat covers his forehead, and he looks utterly bewildered.\n\nMARK\n(Voice tight)\nBut Dr. Fluster, I've been shaking, sweating... and my head feels like cotton wool after a workout.\n\nFluster saunters closer",
